The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     IN THE CITY
                  
	 Chittaranjan High School, Purulia and South Point won the boys and girls team titles, respectively, in the Patterson Memorial table tennis Championship on Tuesday. In the boys final Chittaranjan High School beat Manbhoom Victoria Institution 3-1 while South Point girls blanked St Johns Diacesan 3-0. Riya Dutta beat Moumita Sarkar 11-4, 11-7, 11-5 to win the girls singles title while Anubhav Kundu overcame Ranadip Dutta 11-9, 8-11, 11-4, 11-8 to claim the boys title.          
	 East Bengal have announced their table-tennis team for the inaugural ONGC Bengal Premier League organised by the West Bengal Table Tennis Association. National champions Poulomi Ghatak and Soumyadeep Roy are the most notable names in a team also including Sougata Sarkar, Amit Das, Jayati Pushilal and others. Coach Jayanta Pushilal will be in charge of the team. The tournament starts on Wednesday.           
	 Mridul Bandyopadhyay has been appointed as East Bengals new practice coach. He replaces Alok Mukherjee. It was also announced that Alvito DCunha will be the clubs brand ambassador for the current season.                                                                                                                                                                      
